🔷 PHASE-WISE DEVELOPMENT PLAN

(Progress Tracking Module)

🔵 PHASE 1: REQUIREMENT FINALIZATION (Foundation)
1.1 Objective

To track preschool children’s developmental progress in a non-academic, skill-based, term-wise manner.

1.2 Scope

Track progress for 7 main skill areas

Each main skill has sub-skills

Progress tracked for 3 terms (T1, T2, T3)

Only teachers/admins can mark

Parents can only view

1.3 Assessment Scale (Fixed)
Level	Meaning	Internal Value
Achieved	Performs independently and consistently	3
Approaching	Performs with guidance	2
Needs Support	Requires frequent assistance	1

⚠️ Numeric values are internal only, never shown to parents.

1.4 Progress Calculation Rule
Progress % = (Sum of sub-skill scores) / (Total sub-skills × 3) × 100

Display Rule (Parent View)
% Range	Display Label
0–49	Emerging
50–74	Progressing
75–100	Well Developed
