🔵 PHASE 4: BUSINESS LOGIC & CALCULATION

(HOW the system thinks)

4.1 Progress Calculation Logic
Step-by-step:

Count total sub-skills in a main skill

Multiply by 3 → Maximum Score

Sum marked sub-skill scores → Actual Score

Calculate percentage internally

progress = (actual / maximum) × 100

4.2 Interpretation Layer (Very Important)

Parents never see percentages.

Internal %	Parent Label
0–49	Emerging
50–74	Progressing
75–100	Well Developed
4.3 Assessment Coverage Logic
coverage = assessed_sub_skills / total_sub_skills

Coverage	Display
< 50%	Not Yet Fully Assessed
50–79%	Partially Assessed
≥ 80%	Fully Assessed
4.4 Focus Area Logic

Rule:

Any sub-skill marked Needs Support
→ Automatically shown under Focus Areas

4.5 Trend Logic (Term Comparison)

Compare:

Average score T1 → T2 → T3

Display:

⬆ Improving

➡ Maintaining

⬇ Needs More Support

